<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="411" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3053023308" collectionCode="MNHN" pageId="19" pageNumber="411" specimenCode="MNHN 1933.148, MNHN 1933.149" specimenCount="3" typeStatus="syntype">
The original type series consisted of two 
<typeStatus box="[656,758,151,177]" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">syntypes</typeStatus>
. The second of these, 
<specimenCode box="[1002,1199,151,177]" collectionCode="MNHN" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">MNHN 1933.148</specimenCode>
has a new (red) label that erroneously reads “1933.0149”, but its identity can be clearly assessed based on its paper label. We here designate the larger of the two 
<typeStatus box="[439,540,223,249]" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">syntypes</typeStatus>
, 
<specimenCode box="[551,752,223,249]" collectionCode="MNHN" country="France" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">MNHN 1933.149</specimenCode>
, as 
<typeStatus box="[793,899,223,249]" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">lectotype</typeStatus>
, to allow unambiguous definition of this nomen in case future studies reveal the existence of more than two species in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mocquard" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[978,1113,259,285]" class="Amphibia" family="Microhylidae" genus="Scaphiophryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="19" pageNumber="411" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="calcarata">
<emphasis box="[978,1113,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">S. calcarata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,295,321]" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">Morphology.</emphasis>
The two original 
<typeStatus box="[558,656,295,321]" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">syntypes</typeStatus>
of this nomen (
<bibRefCitation author="Frost, D. R." box="[836,961,295,321]" pageId="19" pageNumber="411" refId="ref16466" refString="Frost, D. R. (2020) Amphibian Species of the World: an Online Reference. Version 6.1. Electronic Database accessible at American Museum of Natural History, New York. Available from: https: // amphibiansoftheworld. amnh. org / index. php (accessed 7 June 2020) https: // doi. org / 10.5531 / db. vz. 0001" type="url" year="2020">Frost 2020</bibRefCitation>
) are in a rather good state of preservation and are clearly assignable to 
<taxonomicName box="[471,639,331,357]" class="Amphibia" family="Microhylidae" genus="Scaphiophryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="19" pageNumber="411" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[471,639,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">Scaphiophryne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the tarsal tubercle and enlarged inner metatarsal tubercle (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[273,1323,191,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@15.[259,1329,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Photographs of the details of morphology of type specimens of the nomina in the genus Scaphiophryne (subgenus Pseudohemisus) except the holotype of S. brevis, showing feet (left column) and hands (middle column) in ventral view, and the head (right column) in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574893/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). They bear clear diagnostic characters of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mocquard" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[673,807,367,393]" class="Amphibia" family="Microhylidae" genus="Scaphiophryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="19" pageNumber="411" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="calcarata">
<emphasis box="[673,807,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">S. calcarata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex, particularly, a dorsolateral ridge running along the entire body.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">
Osteological examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[571,674,439,465]" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">lectotype</typeStatus>
revealed close resemblance to the other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mocquard" authorityYear="1895" box="[1138,1311,439,465]" class="Amphibia" family="Microhylidae" genus="Pseudohemisus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="19" pageNumber="411" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1138,1311,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">Pseudohemisus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens examined here (
<figureCitation box="[331,413,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[155,1425,1213,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-393@19.[151,1436,1209,1909]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 10. Micro-CT scans of the name-bearing type specimens of nomina in the subgenus Scaphiophryne (Pseudohemisus) except the holotype of S. brevis: skulls in dorsal, ventral and lateral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574895/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
, Supplementary 
<figureCitation box="[601,720,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1887,1911]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,181,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[151,1436,181,1863]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Haplotype networks based on DNA sequences of two nuclear genes, POMC (310 bp) and RAG-1 (788 bp) for species of Scaphiophryne and Paradoxophyla. Small black circles represent additional mutational steps between identified haplotypes. Colors of taxa correspond to those in Fig. 1." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574875" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574875/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">Figs S2–S</figureCitation>
<figureCitation box="[720,733,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[174,1405,181,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-17@8.[174,1413,181,1831]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. Individuals in life of the three species of Scaphiophryne in the subgenus Pseudohemisus according to the classification proposed in the present paper: Scaphiophryne brevis from Ifaty (A–E), Kirindy (F–G) and Isalo (H); S. calcarata from Pic St. Louis near Tolagnaro (I–K), Ambalavao (L), Isalo (Ilakaka) (M–N), Sakaviro (O) and near Anja (P); S. obscura from Isalo (Q), Kirindy (R–V), Ankarafantsika (W), and Bongolava Plateau (X). Photos by F. Glaw, J. Lobon-Rovira, A. Miralles, G. M. Rosa, and M. Vences." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574877/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,346,510,536]" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">Assignment.</emphasis>
As with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Angel" authorityYear="1930" box="[455,769,511,537]" class="Amphibia" family="Microhylidae" genus="Pseudohemisus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="19" pageNumber="411" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longimanus">
<emphasis box="[455,769,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">Pseudohemisus longimanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[828,876,511,537]" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">type</typeStatus>
locality of this nomen is in an area between the known ranges of the western and the north-western lineage of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Grandidier" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[840,958,547,573]" class="Amphibia" family="Microhylidae" genus="Scaphiophryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="19" pageNumber="411" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis box="[840,958,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">S. obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. While it is therefore not possible to assign the nomen to either of these intraspecific lineages, based on its provenance we propose considering 
<taxonomicName authority="Angel, 1934 a" authorityName="Angel" authorityYear="1934" class="Amphibia" family="Microhylidae" genus="Pseudohemisus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="19" pageNumber="411" phylum="Chordata" rank="variety" species="longimanus" variety="melanopleura">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">Pseudohemisus longimanus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[337,493,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">melanopleura</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Angel, F." box="[498,636,619,645]" pageId="19" pageNumber="411" pagination="169 - 172" refId="ref15602" refString="Angel, F. (1934) Description d'un Viperide nouveau du Congo Belge et de deux batraciens de Madagascar. Bulletin de la Societe Zoologique de France, 59, 169 - 172." type="journal article" year="1934">Angel, 1934</bibRefCitation>
a
</taxonomicName>
junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Grandidier" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[877,1142,619,645]" class="Amphibia" family="Microhylidae" genus="Scaphiophryne" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="19" pageNumber="411" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis box="[877,1142,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="411">Scaphiophryne obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
